[2026-03-09T15:45:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QkNXrgQ2APehExEaffZWtT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of how logs are displayed. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of Run Log Display in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's how run logs are stored, retrieved, and displayed:\n\n### 1. **Log Storage and Architecture**\n\n**Multi-layer logging system:**\n- **Full unified log**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log` - A single consolidated log file with all events\n- **Per-step logs**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/{step-name}.log` - Individual step output\n- **Container log**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/container.log` - Raw container stdout/stderr\n- **Indexed database**: SQLite `log_files` table tracks all logs with metadata\n\n**Log format (full.log)**: \n```\n[timestamp] [type] content\n```\nWhere type can be: \"status\", \"script\", or \"llm\"\n\n### 2. **Core Log Types and Interfaces**\n\n**Ports (Interfaces):**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`:\n  - `LogStore` interface with methods:\n    - `SaveLogFile()` - Save log file entry to database\n    - `GetLogFiles()` - Retrieve all logs for a run\n    - `GetLogFilesByStep()` - Retrieve logs for specific step\n    - `GetLogFileByType()` - Retrieve logs by type (script, llm, full)\n\n- `CaptureStore` interface:\n  - `SaveCapture()` - Save step execution metadata\n  - `GetCaptures()` - Retrieve step execution history\n\n**Domain types:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - `StepExecution` struct with:\n  - `StepName`, `Result`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n  - `Logs` field for log content\n  - `GitRef` for output branch reference\n\n### 3. **Log Writing Pipeline**\n\n**Log stream writer** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`):\n- `Writer` struct with concurrent-safe logging\n- `Log(type, message)` method writes timestamped, type-prefixed entries\n- Writes to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Supports multi-line messages (splits into separate timestamped entries)\n\n**Log broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n- `Broadcaster` manages real-time log streams for active runs\n- `LogLine` struct: `{Timestamp, Type, Content}`\n- `Subscriber` pattern with buffered channels (256 buffer)\n- Thread-safe publish/subscribe for live log streaming\n- `Finish()` closes all subscribers when run completes\n\n### 4. **Database Storage**\n\n**SQLite implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`):\n\nLog files table:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE log_files (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  step_name TEXT,\n  file_type TEXT,        -- \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n  file_path TEXT NOT NULL,\n  file_size INTEGER,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n)\n```\n\nStep executions table:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE step_executions (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  run_id TEXT,\n  step_name TEXT,\n  result TEXT,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  logs TEXT,             -- Step log content\n  git_ref TEXT\n)\n```\n\n### 5. **Web Handler - Log Display**\n\n**Key handlers** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`:\n\n1. **`handleAPIStepOutput()`** (lines 563-634):\n   - Serves individual step output\n   - Lookup priority:\n     1. Log index (fast database lookup by step)\n     2. `llm-{step}.log` if type=\"llm\"\n     3. `{step}.log` per-step output\n     4. `container.log` fallback\n     5. Live docker logs (if container still exists)\n\n2. **`handleAPIStream()`** (lines 716-775):\n   - Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming endpoint\n   - For **active runs**: Subscribes to broadcaster, sends live log lines\n   - For **completed runs**: Reads archived full.log and streams as JSON events\n   - Sends \"done\" event when complete\n\n3. **`streamFullLog()`** (lines 781-797):\n   - Reads full.log line by line\n   - Parses format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n   - Sends each line as JSON SSE data event\n\n4. **`mergeCaptures()`** (lines 306-348):\n   - Merges step_started/step_completed execution records\n   - Calculates duration, creates UI entries\n\n### 6. **Web UI Templates**\n\n**Run detail template** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`):\n\n**Live log viewer** (lines 62-66):\n```html\n<h2>Log <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\">Live</span></h2>\n<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n```\n\n**Log streaming JavaScript** (lines 69-123):\n- Connects to `/api/runs/{id}/stream` EventSource\n- Receives JSON log lines: `{timestamp, type, content}`\n- Auto-scrolls unless user manually scrolls up\n- Handles both live and archived logs\n- Colors logs by type via CSS class `log-type-{type}`\n\n**Steps table** (lines 33-60):\n- Shows step execution history with timing\n- Expandable rows showing step output via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Polls for updates every 2 seconds for active runs (lines 126-180)\n\n**Runs list template** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`):\n- Displays run history with state, timing, container info\n- Polls `/api/runs` for updates every 3 seconds\n\n### 7. **Key Files Location**\n\n**Storage/Retrieval:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Interface definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - Database implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/history.go` - Local history logging\n\n**Streaming:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` - Log writer\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - Live streaming\n\n**Web Display:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - HTTP handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Log viewer UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Run history UI\n\n### 8. **Log Parsing Logic**\n\n**Regex pattern** (handler.go line 778):\n```go\nvar logLineRegex = regexp.MustCompile(`^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`)\n```\n\nParses: `[2025-01-15T10:30:45Z] [script] your log message`\n\nThis enables flexible log display with proper timestamp and type classification."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0c395ffdc9436911 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59814\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 51235</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e316c9bd-e648-4c15-80fc-32844599c155","uuid":"fec5903b-73e1-4454-ac5a-eafe9345a96d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find how run logs are displayed in this Go project. Look for:\n1. How logs are stored and retrieved (look in internal/adapters/ and internal/ports/)\n2. How logs are displayed in the web UI (look in internal/adapters/web/)\n3. Any existing log parsing logic\n4. The web handler that serves run logs/history\n5. The templates that render run history\n\nSearch for keywords like \"logs\", \"capture\", \"history\", \"stream\", \"jsonl\" across the codebase. Be thorough - check handler.go, any template files, and the domain types.","agentId":"a0c395ffdc9436911","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of how logs are displayed. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of Run Log Display in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's how run logs are stored, retrieved, and displayed:\n\n### 1. **Log Storage and Architecture**\n\n**Multi-layer logging system:**\n- **Full unified log**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log` - A single consolidated log file with all events\n- **Per-step logs**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/{step-name}.log` - Individual step output\n- **Container log**: `/workspace/.cloche/{run-id}/output/container.log` - Raw container stdout/stderr\n- **Indexed database**: SQLite `log_files` table tracks all logs with metadata\n\n**Log format (full.log)**: \n```\n[timestamp] [type] content\n```\nWhere type can be: \"status\", \"script\", or \"llm\"\n\n### 2. **Core Log Types and Interfaces**\n\n**Ports (Interfaces):**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`:\n  - `LogStore` interface with methods:\n    - `SaveLogFile()` - Save log file entry to database\n    - `GetLogFiles()` - Retrieve all logs for a run\n    - `GetLogFilesByStep()` - Retrieve logs for specific step\n    - `GetLogFileByType()` - Retrieve logs by type (script, llm, full)\n\n- `CaptureStore` interface:\n  - `SaveCapture()` - Save step execution metadata\n  - `GetCaptures()` - Retrieve step execution history\n\n**Domain types:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - `StepExecution` struct with:\n  - `StepName`, `Result`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n  - `Logs` field for log content\n  - `GitRef` for output branch reference\n\n### 3. **Log Writing Pipeline**\n\n**Log stream writer** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`):\n- `Writer` struct with concurrent-safe logging\n- `Log(type, message)` method writes timestamped, type-prefixed entries\n- Writes to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Supports multi-line messages (splits into separate timestamped entries)\n\n**Log broadcaster** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n- `Broadcaster` manages real-time log streams for active runs\n- `LogLine` struct: `{Timestamp, Type, Content}`\n- `Subscriber` pattern with buffered channels (256 buffer)\n- Thread-safe publish/subscribe for live log streaming\n- `Finish()` closes all subscribers when run completes\n\n### 4. **Database Storage**\n\n**SQLite implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`):\n\nLog files table:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE log_files (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  step_name TEXT,\n  file_type TEXT,        -- \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n  file_path TEXT NOT NULL,\n  file_size INTEGER,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n)\n```\n\nStep executions table:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE step_executions (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n  run_id TEXT,\n  step_name TEXT,\n  res