[2026-03-09T15:45:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JE9UJk7Qn7SCWy46tFhWVs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→All changes implemented and tests passing. Here's a summary:\n     2→\n     3→### Changes made\n     4→\n     5→1. **`internal/ports/container.go`** — Added `Logs(ctx, containerID) (string, error)` to the `ContainerRuntime` interface.\n     6→\n     7→2. **`internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`** — Implemented `Logs()` by running `docker logs <containerID>` and returning combined stdout+stderr.\n     8→\n     9→3. **`internal/adapters/local/runtime.go`** — Implemented a no-op `Logs()` that returns `(\"\", nil)`.\n    10→\n    11→4. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Two changes:\n    12→   - In `trackRun()`: after `CopyFrom` extracts step outputs and before `Remove()`, calls `s.container.Logs()` and writes the result to `.cloche/<runID>/output/container.log`.\n    13→   - In `StreamLogs()`: when reading per-step output, if the file is missing or empty, falls back to reading `container.log`.\n    14→\n    15→5. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`** — Added two tests:\n    16→   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_FallsBackToContainerLog` — verifies that when no per-step output exists, `container.log` content is returned in the step_completed entry.\n    17→   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_PrefersStepOutput` — verifies that when per-step output exists, it takes priority over `container.log`.\n    18→\n    19→CLOCHE_RESULT:success\n    20→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LbJUrEpKUsTxPgt13TBUr4","session_id":"e316c9bd-e648-4c15-80fc-32844599c155","uuid":"f73ba940-83bb-49e5-9706-df92e4da79ca"}
