[2026-03-09T15:45:16Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LbJUrEpKUsTxPgt13TBUr4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary: Claude Code Agent Output Capture in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how Claude Code agent output is captured and stored:\n\n### 1. **Agent Output Format & Capture**\n\n**Raw Output Format:**\n- Claude Code agent is invoked with `--output-format stream-json --verbose` flags (see `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`, line 22)\n- Output is **stream-JSON** format: each line is a JSON event containing either:\n  - `content_block_delta` events with `text_delta` field for streaming text\n  - `result` events with `subtype` for final output containing the `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker\n\n**Capture Location:**\n- In `internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`, method `tryCommand()` (lines 141-218):\n  - Pipes agent stdout through a `bufio.Scanner`\n  - Two buffers are maintained:\n    - **textBuf**: Extracted text content (parsed JSON text deltas)\n    - **rawBuf**: Raw stdout bytes as-is (for the `.log` file)\n\n### 2. **Step Output Files Format (`.log` files)**\n\n**Stored Location:**\n- Path: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.log`\n- Created at lines 120-124 in `prompt.go`\n\n**Content Format:**\n- For agent steps: The **raw stdout** from stream-json format\n- For script steps (generic adapter): Cleaned output with CLOCHE_RESULT markers removed (see `internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`, line 36)\n- Sample content (from `/workspace/.cloche/develop-wise-reef/output/implement.log`):\n  ```\n  All checks pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n  \n  1. **field_name** — Description\n  \n  CLOCHE_RESULT:success\n  ```\n\n### 3. **Result Extraction (JSON Parsing)**\n\n**Location:** `internal/protocol/result.go`\n\n**Extraction Logic:**\n```go\n// ExtractResult scans for last \"CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\" line\n// Returns (resultName, cleanedOutput, found)\n```\n\n**Parser in `prompt.go`:**\n- Line 251-279: `extractStreamText()` function\n- Parses JSON events to extract text content:\n  - Looks for `content_block_delta` events with `text_delta` type\n  - Also extracts final `result` events containing CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- Used in streaming path (line 182) and buffered path (line 212)\n\n### 4. **Two Output Paths**\n\n**With StatusWriter (Live Streaming - lines 158-217):**\n```\nStream JSON → Scanner → Extract Text (rawBuf for file, textBuf for status)\n  ↓\n- Live broadcast via StatusWriter.Log() (line 196)\n- Text deltas extracted and accumulated\n- rawBuf contains full stdout for .log file\n```\n\n**Without StatusWriter (Buffered - lines 148-155):**\n```\nStream JSON → Buffer → Extract Text\n  ↓\n- simpler flow: full stdout buffered\n```\n\n### 5. **Unified Logging: `full.log`**\n\n**Location:** `internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n\n**Format:**\n```\n[2026-03-06T23:25:06Z] [status] error: invalid workflow...\n[2026-03-01T23:26:53Z] [llm] Text content from agent...\n[2026-03-01T23:28:21Z] [script] Build output...\n```\n\n**Entry Types:**\n- `status`: Workflow-level messages\n- `script`: Script/generic adapter output\n- `llm`: Claude Code agent output (parsed text)\n\n**Creation:**\n- Created in `trackRun()` in `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 198-286)\n- Container stdout/stderr collected via `AttachOutput()` and parsed as JSON-lines of `StatusMessage` objects\n- Protocol message types:\n  - `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `log`, `error`\n\n### 6. **History Log Format**\n\n**Location:** `.cloche/history.log`\n\n**Format:**\n```\n[2026-03-01T23:26:53Z] step:implement result:success (agent)\n\n[2026-03-01T23:28:21Z] step:test result:fail\n  | Test output line 1\n  | Test output line 2\n\n```\n\n**Key Difference:**\n- Agent steps: Header only (line 23 in `history.go`)\n- Script steps: Header + indented output with `  | ` prefix (line 29)\n\n### 7. **Container Log Fallback**\n\n**Location:** `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n\n**When Created:**\n- In `trackRun()` line 281 of `grpc/server.go`\n- Calls `s.container.Logs()` to get full container stdout/stderr\n- Used as fallback when step output is missing (line 524 in `grpc/server.go`)\n\n### 8. **Status Message Protocol**\n\n**Format:** JSON-lines sent from agent to daemon\n\n**Message Structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"log\",\n  \"step_name\": \"implement\",\n  \"message\": \"Claude: Analyzing code...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-01T23:28:21.012530256Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Parsed in `protocol/status.go`:**\n- Types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `log`, `error`\n- Unmarshaled as `StatusMessage` struct\n\n### 9. **Log File Index**\n\n**Port Interface:** `LogStore` in `internal/ports/store.go`\n\n**Tracked Metadata:**\n- `RunID`, `StepName`, `FileType` (full, script, llm)\n- `FilePath`, `FileSize`, `CreatedAt`\n\n**Indexing Logic:** `indexLogFiles()` in `grpc/server.go` (lines 705-757)\n- Scans `.cloche/<runID>/output/` directory\n- Determines type by filename pattern:\n  - `full.log` → type=\"full\"\n  - `llm-<step>.log` → type=\"llm\", stepName=<step>\n  - `<step>.log` → type=\"script\", stepName=<step>\n  - `container.log` → not indexed (internal)\n\n### 10. **Web Streaming (SSE)**\n\n**Handler:** `handleAPIStream()` in `internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 716-775)\n\n**For Completed Runs:**\n- Reads archived `full.log` \n- Parses `[timestamp] [type] content` format using regex\n- Converts to `LogLine` JSON objects\n- Streams as Server-Sent Events (SSE)\n\n**For Active Runs:**\n- Subscribes to `logBroadcast` broadcaster\n- Receives `LogLine` objects in real-time\n- Sends as SSE events\n\n### Key Files & Paths\n\n| Purpose | Path |\n|---------|------|\n| Agent adapter (prompt) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` |\n| Result extraction | `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` |\n| Status message protocol | `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` |\n| History logging | `/workspace/internal/protocol/history.go` |\n| Unified logging | `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` |\n| Log broadcaster | `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` |\n| gRPC server (tracking) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` |\n| Web handler (streaming) | `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` |\n| Log store interface | `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a669ad06a670dbffc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51335\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 46195</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e316c9bd-e648-4c15-80fc-32844599c155","uuid":"2837141c-2511-478b-ad88-fba785896515","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In this Go project, find:\n1. How Claude Code agent output is captured - look in internal/adapters/ for agent-related code\n2. What format the raw output is in (JSONL? raw stdout?)\n3. How step output files (.log) are written\n4. Look for any existing JSON parsing of agent output\n5. Check internal/logstream/ for how logs are written\n\nFocus on the agent adapter and how it captures/writes output. Also check for any sample log files in .cloche/ directories to understand the raw format.","agentId":"a669ad06a670dbffc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary: Claude Code Agent Output Capture in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how Claude Code agent output is captured and stored:\n\n### 1. **Agent Output Format & Capture**\n\n**Raw Output Format:**\n- Claude Code agent is invoked with `--output-format stream-json --verbose` flags (see `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`, line 22)\n- Output is **stream-JSON** format: each line is a JSON event containing 